  "response": "Generally speaking, bees are more dangerous to humans than ants. Here's why:\n\n1. Bee stings\n- Can cause severe allergic reactions (anaphylaxis) in some people\n- Each bee can sting multiple times\n- Bee stings are more painful\n- Swarms of bees can be very dangerous\n\n2. Ant interactions\n- Most ant species have relatively mild stings or bites\n- Fire ants can cause painful stings, but they're less likely to cause serious allergic reactions\n- Typically less aggressive than bees\n\nWhile both insects can sting or bite, bees are generally considered more dangerous to humans due to their potential for causing serious allergic reactions and more painful stings.",
